[4] Shigellosis - USA (MI)
Date: Tue 25 Oct 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: WLNS.com [edited]
<http://www.wlns.com/Global/story.asp?S=2473345&nav=0RbQSLSg>

20 confirmed cases of shigellosis at school
---------------------------------------
20 cases of shigellosis have now been confirmed in Lansing. The
announcement comes as Ingham County health officials continue to review
their laboratory results. Shigellosis was 1st discovered early last week
[4th week of October 2004] at Willow Elementary in Lansing.
Health officials say at least 3 of the newly confirmed cases may have been
spread by a person carrying the bacteria. At least 20 more cases are still
being investigated. Now, officials believe the outbreak is under control
and are searching for how it all started. They've been racing against time
to find the origin and prevent future spreading.
Diane Gorch, Supervisor of the Food Safety Program at Ingham Health
Department, said: "We need to get this information in a timely way so we
can get it all in, grind it up and see what we can learn from it."
She's one of 6 people working long hours trying get to the bottom of the
shigellosis outbreak. By making numerous phone calls, and going door to
door, they're gathering information from Willow Elementary students and
their families.
--
